race.comment: HOT MAJESTY (1) is finding the line with gusto this prep, the latest effort a closing third over the mile at this track. Beautifully placed out to this trip third-up and a long win drought might end today. PROCHESTER (2) is an ex-Victorian stayer having his first run under Jack Bruce. Wasn't beaten all that far at his last run seven weeks ago in a BM66 over a 2580m at Cranbourne. Will be better for the run but in this company he is capable of a bright performance while fresh. COOL RUNNING (8) has been run off his legs in two runs this time in work over sprint trips. Yet to be tested beyond a mile but he needs a bit of ground now. Could be the surprise packet with Ange Jones taking over. IN SOCIETY (9) can improve with a step up in journey today.
